cetus.hir
Interface Symbol

All Known Implementing Classes:
AccessSymbol, DerefSymbol, IPPointsToAnalysis.AbstractLocation, NestedDeclarator, Procedure, ProcedureDeclarator, PseudoSymbol, VariableDeclarator
public interface Symbol

An IR object that implements Symbol interface is identified as a unique symbol in the program. Every Identifier object has a link to its corresponding Symbol object and can access the attributes of the symbol object.

setName

void setName(java.lang.String name)
Modify the name of the symbol. This method effectively renames all the identifiers constructed from the symbol object. Pass writers should be cautious when renaming global names since the effective scope of this operation is within a translation unit; extern variables and procedure names are not automatically handled.

Parameters:
name - the new name of the symbol.

getDeclaration

Declaration getDeclaration()
Returns the parent declaration containing the symbol object. The return value is searched from the internal look-up table. Depending on the type of the symbol, this method may return the symbol object itself, or null if the symbol object does not exist in the IR.

Returns:
the parent declaration.
